==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tine
<hw>Tine</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Tind</er>.]</ety> <def>To
kindle; to set on fire.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <see>See
<er>Tind</er>.</see> ⟦ldquo⟧To <xex>tine</xex> the cloven wood.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Coals of contention and hot vengeance <qex>tind</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tine</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Tine
<hw>Tine</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Tine</er> distress, or
<er>Tine</er> to kindle.]</ety> <def>To kindle; to rage; to smart.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ne was there slave, ne was there medicine⟦br⟧
That mote recure their wounds; so inly they did <qex>tine</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tine</ent>⟦br⟧

